If you've been a member in good standing for one full year before an election, you have the opportunity to serve on our prestigious board. Why Join the Board? As a board member, you'll play a crucial role in shaping the future of our chamber and the local business community. You'll have a direct impact on the decisions and initiatives that drive growth, collaboration, and success in Key West. This is your chance to make your voice heard and contribute to the vibrant economic landscape of our region. ​ Eligibility Criteria To be considered for a position on the board, you must meet the following requirements: 1. Membership: You must be a member of the Greater Key West Chamber of Commerce. 2. Good Standing: Your membership must be in good standing for a minimum of one full year before the election. 3. Willingness to Serve: Complete and sign our questionnaire, indicating your desire to serve on the board and contribute to the chamber's mission. 4. Commitment to Attendance: You must commit to attending all required meetings, including the Board of Directors Annual Retreat, regular monthly Board of Directors meetings, monthly General Membership meetings, and the Annual Installation Meeting. Make a Difference Today! Don't miss this chance to take your involvement with the Greater Key West Chamber of Commerce to the next level. Join our board and become an influential advocate for local businesses and entrepreneurs. Together, we can shape a prosperous future for Key West. Ready to Get Started? To express your interest in becoming a board member, please contact Kerry Baker at (305) 294-2587. ​ Join the Greater Key West Chamber of Commerce Board of Directors and make a lasting impact on our business community! end main-wrap Greater Key West Chamber of Commerce.  All Rights Reserved. ﻿ 510 Greene St., First Floor  |  Key West, FL 33040 [email protected] | sitemap end container end footer-wrap Visit Key West Community Calendar Getting Here Map & Places of Interest Places to Stay > Lodging Online Booking Places to Dine Things to Do > The Florida Keys & Key West Weddings Sunset Times Live, Work & Relocate New Residents Guide Important Telephone Numbers City of Key West > Utilities Disaster Preparedness Resources Monroe County > School/College Registration Auto/Drivers License Info Fishing/Hunting/Boating Licenses Info Latest Community News Job Listings > Job Board The Chamber Why Join the Chamber > Membership Application Testimonials Member Login Membership Referral Board of Directors > How to Become A Board Member Chamber Staff Chamber Calendar Committees Chamber Resources > Business Magazine Archive Business Directory Member Discounts and Affinity Programs Awards > Athena Award Nominations Chamber News > Cybersecurity and Ransomware Photo Gallery Blog Contact Us Foundation Tom Sawyer Five Star Program Teacher Appreciation Past Scholarship Award Winners A Guide to Tourist Development Tax for Home Rentals Economic Partners Quick Facts
